1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:05,199
(Previously)
A servant like you has nothing to lose!

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,500
My love has dignity as well!

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:12,700
Focus on your studies and
forget about everything.

4
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,700
(11 Years Later)

5
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:21,699
This is Captain Phobtheera Mankongphak,
representing the main infantry.

6
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:25,700
Nice to meet you, Prince Tinnakorn.

7
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,099
Why didn't Your Highness
watch the performance to the end?

8
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:36,499
Was it because you were thinking of
our past and couldn't bear to watch it?

9
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,940
I already told you that
I have forgotten all of those things.

10
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:12,200
"The Edge of Horizon"
(Episode 4)

11
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:32,701
Oh, hey.

12
00:02:38,737 --> 00:02:40,062
Do you want to try it?

13
00:02:42,702 --> 00:02:46,182
I don't think so,
I don't want to break your camera.

14
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:50,022
You're so great.

15
00:02:50,390 --> 00:02:52,662
You can write and you can take photos.

16
00:02:53,502 --> 00:02:55,262
I want to be good at something like you.

17
00:02:56,982 --> 00:03:00,022
Oh dear, why do you want to be like me?

18
00:03:00,662 --> 00:03:02,502
I should be the one who's jealous of you.

19
00:03:02,723 --> 00:03:05,782
You have everything;
the look, the noble title

20
00:03:06,462 --> 00:03:09,062
and your perfect date
like Prince Tinnakorn.

21
00:03:15,422 --> 00:03:16,942
Is everything okay?

22
00:03:23,825 --> 00:03:25,724
Hi, Siri.

23
00:03:26,332 --> 00:03:27,333
There you are.

24
00:03:28,022 --> 00:03:30,062
I got caught up at work
so I was late to the show.

25
00:03:30,977 --> 00:03:32,942
Well, who is this?

26
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:37,582
Chat, this is Ms. Janthorn.

27
00:03:37,752 --> 00:03:39,753
She's a journalist from Lok Siam newspaper.

28
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:42,142
A journalist from Lok… Siam?

29
00:03:44,222 --> 00:03:45,426
It's you!

30
00:03:45,848 --> 00:03:48,408
You've constantly dragged my name
through the mud in your paper!

31
00:03:50,444 --> 00:03:52,302
Give it to me! Give it to me now.

32
00:03:52,412 --> 00:03:53,842
- It's mine.
- Let it go.

33
00:03:54,033 --> 00:03:56,302
- Give it to me.
- It's mine.

34
00:03:56,390 --> 00:03:57,667
- Let it go.
- Give it back to me.

35
00:03:57,691 --> 00:04:00,054
- Let it go and give it to me.
- It's mine.

36
00:04:00,166 --> 00:04:03,462
- Janthorn?
- Did you take a photo of me? Give it to me.

37
00:04:03,527 --> 00:04:05,062
- Give it to me.
- It's mine.

38
00:04:05,156 --> 00:04:07,822
Let me see, what photos did you take?

39
00:04:07,924 --> 00:04:09,422
What are you doing?

40
00:04:09,604 --> 00:04:13,422
Didn't you know that she's a journalist
from Lok Siam newspaper?

41
00:04:15,601 --> 00:04:17,324
They attacked the government

42
00:04:17,580 --> 00:04:19,062
and royal family members like us.

43
00:04:19,617 --> 00:04:22,342
I only write facts,
I didn't attack anyone.

44
00:04:22,801 --> 00:04:25,142
What facts? You're such a smart mouth.

45
00:04:26,562 --> 00:04:28,182
You're jealous of someone like us.

46
00:04:31,732 --> 00:04:32,733
Give it to me!

47
00:04:33,790 --> 00:04:35,422
Judging from your actions,

48
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:37,982
I think you deserved all
those bad words about you.

49
00:04:38,435 --> 00:04:41,155
You bullied a woman in broad daylight.

50
00:04:41,588 --> 00:04:42,589
Phob!

51
00:04:44,377 --> 00:04:47,302
You're taking her side?

52
00:04:50,042 --> 00:04:53,062
You lowlife scumbags!

53
00:04:54,022 --> 00:04:55,382
People like you

54
00:04:55,454 --> 00:04:57,502
have never done anything
to benefit the nation!

55
00:04:58,982 --> 00:05:00,712
You're useless!

56
00:05:02,654 --> 00:05:03,982
You're speaking as if

57
00:05:05,022 --> 00:05:07,023
you own a nation.

58
00:05:08,502 --> 00:05:11,462
This land is not reserved
only for royal family members.

59
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:13,742
It belongs to everyone

60
00:05:14,084 --> 00:05:15,924
who gave their blood
and sweat to the nation,

61
00:05:17,322 --> 00:05:18,782
including servants

62
00:05:19,423 --> 00:05:20,424
like us.

63
00:05:22,380 --> 00:05:25,302
Noble people who take advantage of

64
00:05:25,505 --> 00:05:28,506
and tyrannize people of lower status
deserve to be called useless.

65
00:05:28,582 --> 00:05:30,502
- Phob!
- Chat, let go.

66
00:05:31,419 --> 00:05:33,262
People are watching you.

67
00:05:33,353 --> 00:05:35,142
You're not ashamed of that?

68
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:49,382
Are you alright?

69
00:06:02,932 --> 00:06:05,212
I'm sorry about my brother's behavior.

70
00:06:06,206 --> 00:06:08,742
If there is anything
broken, please let me know.

71
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,521
I'm happy to be responsible for that.

72
00:06:11,105 --> 00:06:12,542
Nothing is damaged.

73
00:06:14,028 --> 00:06:17,342
You're nothing like your brother.

74
00:06:20,764 --> 00:06:22,862
How are you going back home?

75
00:06:23,745 --> 00:06:25,132
Can I give you a ride?

76
00:06:25,238 --> 00:06:28,502
So you can see the doctor
and check if you're hurt.

77
00:06:28,942 --> 00:06:29,943
It's okay.

78
00:06:30,401 --> 00:06:32,049
Phob can give me a ride.

79
00:06:32,305 --> 00:06:33,942
I'll stop at his place for dinner first.

80
00:06:38,742 --> 00:06:41,782
How long have you two been close friends?

81
00:06:42,377 --> 00:06:45,054
We've been friends since...

82
00:06:45,124 --> 00:06:47,342
Phob left Varakulvatin Palace for a while.

83
00:06:47,748 --> 00:06:49,982
Phob and his mom lived in Ayutthaya

84
00:06:50,249 --> 00:06:52,502
but one of the noblemen
scammed their rental.

85
00:06:52,526 --> 00:06:53,962
His hand got slashed so bad.

86
00:06:57,702 --> 00:06:58,703
Where is my money?

87
00:06:58,865 --> 00:07:00,302
It's not time to pay yet.

88
00:07:04,462 --> 00:07:07,222
Oh my goodness!

89
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:10,180
No! Don't break my things!

90
00:07:10,308 --> 00:07:12,302
Don't break them! Oh my!

91
00:07:15,670 --> 00:07:17,606
Stop! Don't hurt my son.

92
00:07:18,144 --> 00:07:19,902
- Phob, are you okay?
- Mom!

93
00:07:22,092 --> 00:07:23,502
- Phob!
- Where's the money?

94
00:07:23,588 --> 00:07:26,162
I'll get you the money, don't hurt my son.

95
00:07:28,241 --> 00:07:30,782
Here, take it all. You can have it all.

96
00:07:30,828 --> 00:07:32,829
Don't hurt my son! Please!

97
00:07:33,489 --> 00:07:34,782
That's it.

98
00:07:35,942 --> 00:07:36,943
Let's go.

99
00:07:40,420 --> 00:07:41,421
Phob!

100
00:07:41,582 --> 00:07:42,942
How are you?

101
00:07:51,884 --> 00:07:53,862
- His hand got slashed?
- That's right.

102
00:07:58,622 --> 00:07:59,842
When he filed a complaint,

103
00:08:00,060 --> 00:08:02,861
they falsely accused him
and he almost went to jail.

104
00:08:03,197 --> 00:08:05,422
Auntie Nual struggled
so hard to help her son

105
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:07,782
and her valuables were all sold.

106
00:08:08,161 --> 00:08:10,422
That's why they moved to Bangkapi

107
00:08:10,462 --> 00:08:12,062
and met me.

108
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:17,062
He struggled that bad?

109
00:08:17,902 --> 00:08:21,063
Yes. Good for him that
he is an excellent student.

110
00:08:21,241 --> 00:08:24,262
So he passed the test to be a soldier
and won a scholarship to France.

111
00:08:29,782 --> 00:08:32,982
I heard from Princess Ruethaisiri
that when he lived in the palace,

112
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:35,462
you two were close, right?

113
00:08:37,102 --> 00:08:40,103
I guess we both are his best friends.

114
00:08:40,903 --> 00:08:41,942
I don't think so.

115
00:08:43,521 --> 00:08:46,542
You were with him when
he had a hard time in life.

116
00:08:48,342 --> 00:08:50,862
Instead, I was the one
who gave him the hard time.

117
00:09:03,817 --> 00:09:04,818
So tasty.

118
00:09:06,142 --> 00:09:07,143
Everything is so good.

119
00:09:09,598 --> 00:09:10,599
Let me help you.

120
00:09:14,601 --> 00:09:17,222
Your cooking skill has
never changed, still so good.

121
00:09:18,329 --> 00:09:20,182
You're such a sweet talker, always.

122
00:09:20,902 --> 00:09:24,142
I should cook a beef spicy salad for you.

123
00:09:24,742 --> 00:09:26,382
Please? Thank you.

124
00:09:32,281 --> 00:09:33,542
Now you're talking nicely.

125
00:09:42,092 --> 00:09:44,542
You look so tense, what is on your mind?

126
00:09:45,532 --> 00:09:47,222
Are you thinking about Prince Tinnakorn?

127
00:09:51,702 --> 00:09:52,703
Nonsense.

128
00:09:53,238 --> 00:09:54,598
Why would I be thinking about him?

129
00:09:57,982 --> 00:09:59,622
I can tell

130
00:09:59,909 --> 00:10:02,362
that you two were close once.

131
00:10:03,302 --> 00:10:05,222
He is a conservative

132
00:10:05,503 --> 00:10:07,422
and we are progressives.

133
00:10:08,395 --> 00:10:11,595
You two were friends who
stood on different sides,

134
00:10:11,863 --> 00:10:13,464
it must be so awkward.

135
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:17,582
You can't go soft on him.

136
00:10:17,993 --> 00:10:20,062
We still need information
from Prince Tinnakorn.

137
00:10:20,462 --> 00:10:21,463
Do you understand?

138
00:10:23,822 --> 00:10:24,823
I know.

139
00:10:25,772 --> 00:10:27,422
I will go to see him tomorrow

140
00:10:28,102 --> 00:10:29,622
and I will get it done.

141
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:32,709
Hey!

142
00:10:34,622 --> 00:10:36,582
You went to see Prince Tinnakorn?

143
00:10:52,673 --> 00:10:53,674
Phob.

144
00:10:55,052 --> 00:10:56,902
Why do you need to see him again?

145
00:10:59,502 --> 00:11:01,742
Mom, I told you. It's just for work.

146
00:11:03,182 --> 00:11:06,383
The military needs to help him
with the Phra Nakhon celebration.

147
00:11:10,702 --> 00:11:11,862
Are you sure about that?

148
00:11:18,772 --> 00:11:19,782
Don't you worry.

149
00:11:20,884 --> 00:11:21,942
Prince Tinnakorn

150
00:11:23,942 --> 00:11:25,542
will be engaged to Princess Ruethaisiri.

151
00:11:28,358 --> 00:11:29,359
He's forgetten about me,

152
00:11:30,562 --> 00:11:31,942
all about me.

153
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:35,842
There is no bond left between us.

154
00:11:38,422 --> 00:11:39,423
What about you?

155
00:11:41,502 --> 00:11:42,702
Did you forget about him?

156
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:52,271
Phob.

157
00:11:53,735 --> 00:11:55,855
You need to forget

158
00:11:57,702 --> 00:11:59,022
what hurt you.

159
00:12:01,392 --> 00:12:02,402
Your wish

160
00:12:03,422 --> 00:12:05,162
can never come true.

161
00:12:07,729 --> 00:12:10,142
The sky is high and the ground is low.

162
00:12:11,782 --> 00:12:15,462
We live in a different
world than he does.

163
00:12:28,292 --> 00:12:30,302
It doesn't have to always be like that.

164
00:12:36,926 --> 00:12:38,102
What do you mean?

165
00:13:05,325 --> 00:13:06,326
Chat?

166
00:13:06,988 --> 00:13:09,089
About the soldiers'
reimbursement that Phob asked you,

167
00:13:09,113 --> 00:13:10,193
you took care of it, right?

168
00:13:10,782 --> 00:13:12,313
It's all done, Dad.

169
00:13:12,736 --> 00:13:13,737
Good.

170
00:13:14,148 --> 00:13:15,622
Don't embarrass me again.

171
00:13:30,182 --> 00:13:31,462
Janthorn's article

172
00:13:32,342 --> 00:13:34,782
encouraged people to speak up
what they used to be afraid of.

173
00:13:36,310 --> 00:13:37,711
The wind is on our side.

174
00:13:40,942 --> 00:13:43,862
We need to start our mission on the
celebration day as our original plan.

175
00:13:44,702 --> 00:13:45,862
We can't make a mistake.

176
00:13:47,222 --> 00:13:50,223
We need to know the schedule of
all royal family members, in every detail.

177
00:13:50,862 --> 00:13:53,062
We need to know what
places they will visit,

178
00:13:53,308 --> 00:13:56,063
when they will visit and
who will be around them.

179
00:13:57,742 --> 00:14:00,182
If you want a schedule, then it is easy.

180
00:14:00,582 --> 00:14:01,983
Like we discussed earlier,

181
00:14:02,422 --> 00:14:04,323
Phob was close to Prince Tinnakorn.

182
00:14:04,662 --> 00:14:05,988
He grew up in the palace.

183
00:14:09,663 --> 00:14:11,622
It's time for Siam's transition.

184
00:14:13,522 --> 00:14:15,302
You're our hope.

185
00:14:26,193 --> 00:14:27,194
Yes, sir.

186
00:14:36,782 --> 00:14:38,539
[M.C. Tinnakorn Varakulvatin -
His Majesty's Principal Private Secretary]

187
00:14:38,563 --> 00:14:39,564
What?

188
00:14:40,162 --> 00:14:43,202
You're asking for the royal family
member's schedule on celebration day?

189
00:14:44,702 --> 00:14:46,103
Why is it related to your job?

190
00:14:46,777 --> 00:14:47,822
I need to know

191
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:50,462
so I can provide protection to all of them.

192
00:14:51,292 --> 00:14:52,293
Provide protection?

193
00:14:53,542 --> 00:14:54,543
From who?

194
00:14:58,148 --> 00:14:58,949
Do you believe that

195
00:14:59,012 --> 00:15:01,582
someone would be dissatisfied
and they would start to protest?

196
00:15:01,881 --> 00:15:03,102
It is possible.

197
00:15:03,622 --> 00:15:05,062
People are in distress,

198
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:06,732
people are stuggling to live.

199
00:15:07,294 --> 00:15:08,654
In the meantime, some noble people

200
00:15:08,862 --> 00:15:11,962
focus on organizing fancy parties
and neglect those who are beneath them.

201
00:15:12,294 --> 00:15:15,394
This could be considered as taking
advantage of people living in lower status.

202
00:15:15,418 --> 00:15:17,142
All of us are not the same.

203
00:15:18,903 --> 00:15:20,904
You lived in Varakulvatin Palace,

204
00:15:21,542 --> 00:15:23,262
- and it provided for you.
- That's right.

205
00:15:25,102 --> 00:15:26,262
I remember it so well.

206
00:15:27,362 --> 00:15:28,563
It provided for me,

207
00:15:30,196 --> 00:15:31,512
but it took something from me.

208
00:15:34,262 --> 00:15:35,382
It got destroyed to pieces.

209
00:15:40,676 --> 00:15:41,677
Where are you going?

210
00:15:42,548 --> 00:15:44,262
Why are you trying to avoid this subject?

211
00:15:49,097 --> 00:15:50,098
What's wrong?

212
00:15:51,422 --> 00:15:52,902
We used to be even closer than this.

213
00:15:54,153 --> 00:15:55,953
Are you sure you want
to forget all about it?

214
00:15:58,382 --> 00:15:59,383
That's right.

215
00:16:00,462 --> 00:16:01,662
I don't remember a thing.

216
00:16:13,398 --> 00:16:14,399
Your past

217
00:16:15,062 --> 00:16:16,342
could mean nothing to you.

218
00:16:17,262 --> 00:16:18,263
That's right.

219
00:16:19,763 --> 00:16:21,302
You should forget about it too.

220
00:16:22,664 --> 00:16:23,725
It meant nothing.

221
00:16:24,501 --> 00:16:26,381
If you forgot all about it,

222
00:16:27,422 --> 00:16:28,943
do you want me to remind you?

223
00:16:32,262 --> 00:16:33,263
Let me go.

224
00:16:37,763 --> 00:16:39,022
If you want me to let you go,

225
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:42,942
your voice needs to be stronger than this.

226
00:17:23,572 --> 00:17:24,902
This one is pretty.

227
00:17:25,204 --> 00:17:27,822
I know, right? I think so, too.

228
00:17:28,142 --> 00:17:29,662
I like this bright blue.

229
00:17:30,622 --> 00:17:32,623
Thank you so much

230
00:17:32,711 --> 00:17:35,812
for accompanying me to pick our the fabric.

231
00:17:35,822 --> 00:17:38,062
We are just two old ladies,

232
00:17:38,169 --> 00:17:42,302
where we are going and what we pick out

233
00:17:42,465 --> 00:17:43,782
are so outdated.

234
00:17:45,762 --> 00:17:47,502
Who are you calling 'old ladies'?

235
00:17:47,962 --> 00:17:51,142
I'm still young and fresh.

236
00:17:51,390 --> 00:17:53,300
I can walk smoothly.

237
00:17:53,362 --> 00:17:56,102
I can get up and sit back down easily.

238
00:17:56,982 --> 00:17:59,462
I will get you! I will get you good.

239
00:17:59,562 --> 00:18:01,222
Stop with your funny comments already.

240
00:18:01,563 --> 00:18:04,342
We're not at our palace, okay?

241
00:18:07,814 --> 00:18:10,142
I need to look over there.

242
00:18:10,401 --> 00:18:12,782
- Where is it?
- They're so pretty.

243
00:18:15,804 --> 00:18:17,405
- Aum.
- Yes, ma'am?

244
00:18:18,902 --> 00:18:22,262
Phob and Tin

245
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:24,142
were so close when they were young.

246
00:18:25,447 --> 00:18:28,895
Why did Phob leave the palace?

247
00:18:29,529 --> 00:18:32,662
It's because of Phob's mom,

248
00:18:32,836 --> 00:18:35,462
I mean…Captain Phobthee,

249
00:18:35,965 --> 00:18:38,621
she resigned to sell her
products out of the city.

250
00:18:38,910 --> 00:18:41,302
Then we lost touch with her.

251
00:18:42,382 --> 00:18:44,462
They were so close

252
00:18:45,055 --> 00:18:46,056
why did they

253
00:18:47,917 --> 00:18:48,997
lose touch all of a sudden?

254
00:18:49,542 --> 00:18:51,062
Good question, ma'am.

255
00:18:51,522 --> 00:18:53,881
Right in the middle of one night,

256
00:18:54,107 --> 00:18:57,108
Phob sneaked into the palace
to meet Prince Tinnakorn.

257
00:18:57,649 --> 00:19:03,582
But his father forbade all of us to
talk about Phob the next morning.

258
00:19:04,103 --> 00:19:07,822
Before Prince Tinnakorn
left to study in the UK,

259
00:19:08,542 --> 00:19:10,302
he asked me to bring Phob

260
00:19:10,582 --> 00:19:13,102
a letter when he was in Ayutthaya.

261
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:16,262
What letter?

262
00:19:17,482 --> 00:19:19,662
I can't read so I wouldn't know.

263
00:19:19,694 --> 00:19:23,102
If I could read, I'd have read the letter already.

264
00:19:24,398 --> 00:19:25,542
I was just kidding.

265
00:19:27,832 --> 00:19:29,462
Why did you ask?

266
00:19:31,825 --> 00:19:33,342
If you forgot all about it,

267
00:19:34,742 --> 00:19:35,982
do you want me to remind you?

268
00:19:37,922 --> 00:19:38,923
Let me go.

269
00:19:40,288 --> 00:19:41,462
If you want me to let you go,

270
00:19:42,017 --> 00:19:43,822
your voice needs to be stronger than this.

271
00:20:02,518 --> 00:20:04,222
I baked some bread,

272
00:20:04,734 --> 00:20:06,581
but I was too clumsy, I dropped them.

273
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:11,343
Hi, Phob.

274
00:20:12,601 --> 00:20:13,801
I didn't know you were coming.

275
00:20:23,762 --> 00:20:27,062
I just feel like they're
not so close anymore.

276
00:20:27,126 --> 00:20:28,127
That's why I'm asking.

277
00:20:30,881 --> 00:20:32,382
Oh my goodness, my princess.

278
00:20:33,302 --> 00:20:34,542
Excuse me, ma'am.

279
00:20:53,148 --> 00:20:54,201
People are stuggling to live.

280
00:20:54,225 --> 00:20:55,585
In the meantime, some noble people

281
00:20:55,809 --> 00:20:58,902
focus on organizing fancy parties
and neglect those who are beneath them.

282
00:20:59,185 --> 00:21:02,382
This could be considered as taking
advantage of people living in lower status.

283
00:21:37,628 --> 00:21:38,629
Your Highness,

284
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:11,382
you are still the same.

285
00:22:12,622 --> 00:22:15,102
You're a lightweight
and you still like to drink.

286
00:22:17,182 --> 00:22:19,062
I'm not a good drinker like you are.

287
00:22:20,054 --> 00:22:21,854
You can drink all night
and you feel nothing.

288
00:22:26,702 --> 00:22:27,703
I'm sorry.

289
00:22:33,817 --> 00:22:35,262
Why are you apologizing to me?

290
00:22:38,388 --> 00:22:40,822
Janthorn told me that
after you left the palace,

291
00:22:40,862 --> 00:22:42,502
you and your mom had to struggle to live.

292
00:22:43,449 --> 00:22:45,862
A nobleman scammed your rental,

293
00:22:45,902 --> 00:22:47,662
you lost everything
and almost went to jail.

294
00:22:51,284 --> 00:22:53,302
Is that why you hate us so much?

295
00:22:55,401 --> 00:22:56,402
That's right.

296
00:22:57,854 --> 00:22:59,102
We struggled to live.

297
00:23:01,502 --> 00:23:02,982
But the most painful experience

298
00:23:05,312 --> 00:23:07,032
wasn't the fact that I almost went to jail,

299
00:23:08,073 --> 00:23:09,862
or lost everything,

300
00:23:13,289 --> 00:23:14,742
it was that letter.

301
00:23:17,290 --> 00:23:18,291
Phob?

302
00:23:20,073 --> 00:23:21,342
Every letter

303
00:23:22,422 --> 00:23:23,662
on the page

304
00:23:25,284 --> 00:23:26,862
was so cruel and it cut me deep.

305
00:23:29,470 --> 00:23:31,022
I wanted to burn the letter.

306
00:23:32,990 --> 00:23:34,062
But I couldn't

307
00:23:36,991 --> 00:23:38,342
because it was the last thing

308
00:23:39,382 --> 00:23:40,783
that you gave me.

309
00:23:44,622 --> 00:23:46,382
It reminded me of

310
00:23:47,825 --> 00:23:49,182
how stupid I used to be.

311
00:23:52,622 --> 00:23:54,942
I'm sorry for causing you pain.

312
00:23:57,942 --> 00:23:58,943
But I..

313
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:02,962
I still meant every
word I said in the letter.

314
00:24:03,702 --> 00:24:06,822
Both of us should forget everything.

315
00:24:10,762 --> 00:24:11,862
I can forget it.

316
00:24:13,993 --> 00:24:15,902
But you need to prove to me

317
00:24:18,022 --> 00:24:19,662
that you forgot all about it as well.

318
00:24:22,382 --> 00:24:23,383
Prove how?

319
00:25:50,486 --> 00:25:52,022
Are you back, sir?

320
00:25:56,622 --> 00:25:57,623
Oh my!

321
00:25:58,182 --> 00:26:00,183
What bit you?

322
00:26:00,542 --> 00:26:02,962
Look at that, your neck is red.

323
00:26:04,052 --> 00:26:05,053
A mosquito.

324
00:26:06,222 --> 00:26:07,223
Just a mosquito.

325
00:26:08,702 --> 00:26:09,703
A mosquito.

326
00:26:12,624 --> 00:26:15,422
You poor thing, it must be so painful.

327
00:27:03,054 --> 00:27:05,342
Phob and his mom lived in Ayutthaya

328
00:27:05,482 --> 00:27:07,782
but one of the noblemen
scammed their rental.

329
00:27:07,808 --> 00:27:09,312
His hand got slashed so bad.

330
00:27:09,472 --> 00:27:10,782
When he filed a complaint,

331
00:27:10,902 --> 00:27:13,662
they falsely accused him
and he almost went to jail.

332
00:27:14,141 --> 00:27:16,282
Auntie Nual struggled
so hard to help her son

333
00:27:16,478 --> 00:27:18,622
and her valuables were all sold.

334
00:27:19,294 --> 00:27:22,262
You were with him when
he had a hard time in life.

335
00:27:24,132 --> 00:27:26,622
Instead, I was the one
who gave him the hard time.

336
00:27:38,468 --> 00:27:40,302
Your Highness? Sir?

337
00:28:49,401 --> 00:28:52,142
There is an update from the group asking
for the regime change?

338
00:28:53,313 --> 00:28:56,942
I heard that many parties are involved,

339
00:28:57,137 --> 00:28:58,612
including the military,

340
00:28:59,162 --> 00:29:02,763
law graduates, civil officials,

341
00:29:02,772 --> 00:29:03,962
and journalists.

342
00:29:04,918 --> 00:29:08,102
The coordinator is a
soldier from Artillery Division,

343
00:29:08,217 --> 00:29:09,622
he is close to Kitti.

344
00:29:15,465 --> 00:29:16,782
I am Captain Phobtheee

345
00:29:17,622 --> 00:29:19,022
from Artillery Division.

346
00:29:19,823 --> 00:29:22,278
I am representing the division
and I'm here to ask for clarity

347
00:29:22,302 --> 00:29:24,622
about pension payments
for junior rank soldiers.

348
00:29:28,342 --> 00:29:29,782
I don't care who they are,

349
00:29:30,702 --> 00:29:34,222
if they wish to overthrow the regime,
they will face with death penalty.

350
00:29:42,745 --> 00:29:44,022
- Aum?
- Yes, sir?

351
00:29:45,102 --> 00:29:46,142
Has Tin left for work yet?

352
00:29:46,332 --> 00:29:48,542
I haven't seen him.

353
00:29:49,201 --> 00:29:50,382
Is everything okay?

354
00:30:20,078 --> 00:30:21,662
Your Highness! Your Highness!

355
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:24,923
Your Highness!

356
00:30:28,657 --> 00:30:29,658
Let's go.

357
00:30:30,737 --> 00:30:31,738
Your Highness!

358
00:30:33,222 --> 00:30:34,223
Your Highness!

359
00:30:56,932 --> 00:30:57,933
Tin!

360
00:30:59,220 --> 00:31:00,362
What's going on? What?

361
00:31:00,902 --> 00:31:04,262
I saw you and Phob last night,
on Charoenkrung Road.

362
00:31:09,403 --> 00:31:10,404
What?

363
00:31:10,962 --> 00:31:11,963
What did you see?

364
00:31:15,964 --> 00:31:17,702
I saw you get out of Phob's car.

365
00:31:18,044 --> 00:31:19,142
What did you do in his car?

366
00:31:22,545 --> 00:31:23,782
I met him by chance.

367
00:31:25,402 --> 00:31:26,462
What is it?

368
00:31:27,193 --> 00:31:28,762
You two met by chance?

369
00:31:29,262 --> 00:31:30,342
Why did you get in his car?

370
00:31:31,662 --> 00:31:33,162
There was nothing.

371
00:31:33,588 --> 00:31:34,762
We need to work together.

372
00:31:38,382 --> 00:31:39,422
Listen to me.

373
00:31:41,022 --> 00:31:42,862
He is a bad person.

374
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:45,982
He didn't mean well to us.

375
00:31:46,502 --> 00:31:48,542
He didn't care about Dad,
he didn't care about me.

376
00:31:50,844 --> 00:31:53,222
He was a servant
who happened to do great in his career.

377
00:31:53,262 --> 00:31:54,662
That's why he is arrogant.

378
00:31:55,462 --> 00:31:58,742
Therefore, you can't be
around him, you hear me?

379
00:31:58,972 --> 00:32:00,822
He will ruin your reputation,

380
00:32:00,862 --> 00:32:02,262
and our family's reputation.

381
00:32:02,312 --> 00:32:05,313
The only person who is ruining
the family's reputation is you.

382
00:32:06,562 --> 00:32:08,042
You should worry more about yourself.

383
00:32:08,262 --> 00:32:09,262
Don't worry about me.

384
00:32:09,862 --> 00:32:11,362
I was just worried about you.

385
00:32:17,926 --> 00:32:19,702
I'm worried that he could hurt you.

386
00:32:25,145 --> 00:32:26,262
In your eyes,

387
00:32:27,202 --> 00:32:28,722
I must be a really bad brother, right?

388
00:32:29,762 --> 00:32:30,763
No! Hey!

389
00:32:52,684 --> 00:32:54,262
You have a date with Tinnakorn, right?

390
00:32:55,718 --> 00:32:56,719
That's right.

391
00:32:58,422 --> 00:32:59,662
Dad?

392
00:33:00,670 --> 00:33:02,962
What if I didn't want to marry Tin?

393
00:33:05,230 --> 00:33:06,262
Why wouldn't you?

394
00:33:06,708 --> 00:33:08,062
His dad and I had an agreement.

395
00:33:09,793 --> 00:33:11,662
What if he didn't love me?

396
00:33:12,417 --> 00:33:14,382
It doesn't matter if he loves you or not.

397
00:33:15,221 --> 00:33:18,061
Our family needs to be
bonded to the Varakulvatin.

398
00:33:18,812 --> 00:33:21,942
You're a woman, you will
have to marry and have children.

399
00:33:22,337 --> 00:33:23,902
Why did you think about it too much?

400
00:33:25,262 --> 00:33:26,802
I have a friend.

401
00:33:27,510 --> 00:33:30,942
She's a talented woman,
she can do so many things.

402
00:33:31,285 --> 00:33:34,022
She can make a living independently.

403
00:33:34,766 --> 00:33:35,902
That's absurd.

404
00:33:36,666 --> 00:33:38,942
She is a commoner.

405
00:33:39,012 --> 00:33:41,052
Of course, she needs to
work hard to make a living.

406
00:33:42,492 --> 00:33:43,822
You were born in a royal family.

407
00:33:45,137 --> 00:33:47,062
Your duty is to maintain your pride.

408
00:33:47,985 --> 00:33:49,786
You have to marry Tinnakorn.

409
00:34:05,202 --> 00:34:06,203
You?

410
00:34:21,553 --> 00:34:23,062
Hey! What are you doing?

411
00:34:28,006 --> 00:34:29,262
I missed you.

412
00:34:30,732 --> 00:34:31,942
Do you miss me?

413
00:34:32,865 --> 00:34:34,362
Stop doing something crazy.

414
00:34:35,982 --> 00:34:36,983
Something crazy?

415
00:34:38,142 --> 00:34:40,302
- But last night…
- I was drunk last night.

416
00:34:42,657 --> 00:34:43,658
You were drunk?

417
00:34:44,942 --> 00:34:45,982
That's right. I was drunk.

418
00:34:46,422 --> 00:34:47,423
Just drunk.

419
00:34:48,142 --> 00:34:50,382
I used to be drunk like
this when I was a kid.

420
00:34:51,708 --> 00:34:52,862
You should know it well.

421
00:35:01,379 --> 00:35:02,542
We are not drunk right now,

422
00:35:03,982 --> 00:35:05,183
we should prove it

423
00:35:05,934 --> 00:35:07,694
to see if you really
have no feeling for me.

424
00:36:02,579 --> 00:36:04,902
What? You said he just went in.

425
00:36:05,070 --> 00:36:06,422
Why is the door locked?

426
00:36:10,110 --> 00:36:11,822
Siri, I'm inside.

427
00:36:14,267 --> 00:36:15,347
I'll open the door for you.

428
00:36:25,904 --> 00:36:28,182
Hi, Phob. You're here, too?

429
00:36:33,542 --> 00:36:35,712
Siri, how are you doing?

430
00:36:55,284 --> 00:36:57,662
Hi, Phob. You're here, too?

431
00:37:04,022 --> 00:37:06,782
[Speaking French.]

432
00:37:19,836 --> 00:37:22,561
Hello? Are you here for a cup of coffee?

433
00:37:23,969 --> 00:37:25,182
Are you here by yourself?

434
00:37:27,225 --> 00:37:29,162
I was supposed to be here with Tinnakorn

435
00:37:30,337 --> 00:37:31,338
but...

436
00:37:33,002 --> 00:37:34,803
he's busy.

437
00:37:37,193 --> 00:37:38,194
If that so,

438
00:37:38,582 --> 00:37:42,162
can I join you instead of him?

439
00:37:42,827 --> 00:37:44,182
Sure, it would be my pleasure.

440
00:37:56,315 --> 00:37:58,622
Is something bothering you?

441
00:37:59,632 --> 00:38:00,962
You can tell me.

442
00:38:04,590 --> 00:38:07,022
It's about my friend.

443
00:38:08,222 --> 00:38:10,142
She has a fiancé.

444
00:38:10,723 --> 00:38:13,163
But it seems like her fiancé
has fallen in love with someone else.

445
00:38:13,565 --> 00:38:15,255
We can punch his face.

446
00:38:15,646 --> 00:38:17,582
He's a player who hurts a woman's heart.

447
00:38:17,852 --> 00:38:20,022
We can't do that. Well…

448
00:38:20,414 --> 00:38:23,662
he is a really nice guy,
but they're not in love.

449
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:25,582
Also,

450
00:38:27,086 --> 00:38:29,912
my friend only sees him as a brother,

451
00:38:29,942 --> 00:38:31,162
and nothing more.

452
00:38:32,462 --> 00:38:34,582
If they aren't in love to start with,

453
00:38:35,022 --> 00:38:37,262
why were they engaged?

454
00:38:38,285 --> 00:38:40,062
It's about suitability.

455
00:38:40,902 --> 00:38:42,662
Their parents took care of it.

456
00:38:44,903 --> 00:38:46,182
Arranged marriage couple?

457
00:38:48,124 --> 00:38:50,222
I think when two people are not in love,

458
00:38:50,582 --> 00:38:52,742
they won't be happy together.

459
00:38:53,164 --> 00:38:56,222
That is so easy. We can just…

460
00:38:56,542 --> 00:38:58,782
let him be with a person that he loves.

461
00:38:59,084 --> 00:39:00,712
She shouldn't try to keep him around.

462
00:39:02,825 --> 00:39:04,426
You're right about this.

463
00:39:06,657 --> 00:39:09,862
I feel so much better
now that I talked to you.

464
00:39:11,122 --> 00:39:12,123
Well,

465
00:39:12,512 --> 00:39:16,462
can I buy you a cup of
coffee as my way to thank you?

466
00:39:18,953 --> 00:39:19,954
Sure, thanks.

467
00:39:30,481 --> 00:39:31,482
Enjoy yourself.

468
00:39:35,142 --> 00:39:36,942
Hello, are you here by yourself?

469
00:39:38,795 --> 00:39:39,796
Welcome.

470
00:39:47,569 --> 00:39:49,782
Sir? How long have you been here?

471
00:39:50,926 --> 00:39:53,822
Right, Sakchai..

472
00:39:54,270 --> 00:39:56,662
- About the money…
- Oh, come on.

473
00:39:57,182 --> 00:39:59,502
We're friends, you can just pay me

474
00:39:59,862 --> 00:40:01,182
when you have enough money.

475
00:40:02,662 --> 00:40:03,812
Actually,

476
00:40:03,822 --> 00:40:06,823
I have something important to tell you.

477
00:40:07,982 --> 00:40:08,983
What is it?

478
00:40:12,241 --> 00:40:13,242
Well,

479
00:40:13,497 --> 00:40:16,302
I heard that a company
owned by British people

480
00:40:16,507 --> 00:40:19,062
is looking for new investors

481
00:40:19,208 --> 00:40:21,162
to invest in mining business in Krabi.

482
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:24,130
Really?

483
00:40:24,182 --> 00:40:25,383
Of course.

484
00:40:26,196 --> 00:40:28,582
I rushed here to tell you this.

485
00:40:28,713 --> 00:40:31,714
If you can invest in the company,

486
00:40:32,465 --> 00:40:34,162
I think we will be so rich.

487
00:40:35,302 --> 00:40:37,702
They will provide 30% of the dividend yield

488
00:40:38,221 --> 00:40:39,582
per month, sir.

489
00:40:39,809 --> 00:40:40,862
That much?

490
00:40:43,166 --> 00:40:44,662
Think about it,

491
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:47,702
if you become a major
shareholder of this mine,

492
00:40:48,025 --> 00:40:51,502
you will be well-known and well-respected.

493
00:40:52,262 --> 00:40:55,062
You will bring great
reputation to your family.

494
00:40:55,162 --> 00:40:56,982
Great reputation to the family.

495
00:40:58,422 --> 00:40:59,983
I don't have that much salary.

496
00:41:00,182 --> 00:41:03,096
- And I still have to pay…
- About that…

497
00:41:03,183 --> 00:41:04,584
don't you worry.

498
00:41:04,942 --> 00:41:07,542
I have a plan for you.

499
00:41:10,254 --> 00:41:13,562
I heard that your ministry
is about to do budget planning?

500
00:41:30,369 --> 00:41:32,862
Did you and Phob talk about
something else besides work?

501
00:41:35,622 --> 00:41:37,142
Why did you want to know?

502
00:41:39,747 --> 00:41:41,088
My people suspected that...

503
00:41:41,686 --> 00:41:44,862
Phob could be a part of the group
wanting a regime change.

504
00:41:47,148 --> 00:41:48,149
Are you sure?

505
00:41:49,502 --> 00:41:50,862
There is no evidence.

506
00:41:52,881 --> 00:41:55,582
Did he say something suspicious?

507
00:41:59,564 --> 00:42:01,422
I'm not sure.

508
00:42:02,702 --> 00:42:04,062
We didn't talk much.

509
00:42:08,022 --> 00:42:09,982
Anyways, you have to be cautious.

510
00:42:11,222 --> 00:42:13,502
If he is acting suspiciously,

511
00:42:13,823 --> 00:42:14,824
you need to tell me.

512
00:42:16,622 --> 00:42:17,623
Yes, Dad.

513
00:42:45,644 --> 00:42:46,645
Your Highness.

514
00:42:50,542 --> 00:42:52,662
Are you here to watch the drill?

515
00:42:53,662 --> 00:42:55,542
The celebration day is
right around the corner.

516
00:42:56,155 --> 00:42:57,956
I need to check the preparations,

517
00:42:58,918 --> 00:43:01,119
in case someone plans to stir something up.

518
00:43:06,049 --> 00:43:09,822
Your division showed
great strength in marching,

519
00:43:10,422 --> 00:43:12,902
I guess Captain Phobthee
should take credit for it.

520
00:43:15,342 --> 00:43:17,262
They should have been
marching with better form.

521
00:43:18,190 --> 00:43:20,222
The soldiers look so exhausted,

522
00:43:21,062 --> 00:43:24,262
and it could be from
delayed pension payment.

523
00:43:25,182 --> 00:43:26,702
It's just a little bit late.

524
00:43:27,033 --> 00:43:28,622
You shouldn't use it as an excuse.

525
00:43:30,289 --> 00:43:32,169
An economic recession
happens across the world,

526
00:43:32,942 --> 00:43:34,943
even the noble people's salaries got cut.

527
00:43:35,662 --> 00:43:39,282
Their salaries got cut but
they have their own assets

528
00:43:39,553 --> 00:43:41,033
to spend for the rest of their lives.

529
00:43:42,593 --> 00:43:44,182
For junior rank officials,

530
00:43:44,972 --> 00:43:46,822
they could be in a mortal situation.

531
00:43:47,558 --> 00:43:50,689
Many of them need to
take care of many people.

532
00:43:51,932 --> 00:43:53,182
It'd be better

533
00:43:53,562 --> 00:43:56,462
if you care about your people.

534
00:43:59,478 --> 00:44:01,102
The noble people have money

535
00:44:01,254 --> 00:44:03,502
because they have been
working hard for generations.

536
00:44:03,964 --> 00:44:05,862
We are not robbing anybody.

537
00:44:06,150 --> 00:44:07,790
It's true that you're not robbing anyone,

538
00:44:09,102 --> 00:44:10,562
but you can live like this

539
00:44:11,246 --> 00:44:13,542
because people in this country are working

540
00:44:14,626 --> 00:44:16,262
so hard to pay taxes.

541
00:44:18,414 --> 00:44:21,462
That's why Rattanakosin
has been flourished for 150 years.

542
00:44:22,182 --> 00:44:23,742
It's true that people pay their taxes.

543
00:44:24,162 --> 00:44:26,222
Bur our Kings guided the nation

544
00:44:26,263 --> 00:44:28,462
and Siam has never been
colonized by anybody.

545
00:44:29,214 --> 00:44:32,222
Also, Siam's honor can compete
with other civilized nations.

546
00:44:34,025 --> 00:44:35,222
We have never been colonized.

547
00:44:37,107 --> 00:44:38,822
But we lost extraterritoriality.

548
00:44:40,036 --> 00:44:41,596
Siamese needs to attend Western courts.

549
00:44:43,022 --> 00:44:44,422
I don't think that would look good.

550
00:44:45,462 --> 00:44:46,463
That's fine.

551
00:44:47,289 --> 00:44:49,142
People have freedom to express their ideas.

552
00:44:50,390 --> 00:44:52,591
They need to fulfill
their duties to the fullest

553
00:44:53,086 --> 00:44:55,187
and organize the
celebration to show our pride.

554
00:44:56,342 --> 00:44:58,822
We are all Siam's officials.

555
00:44:59,902 --> 00:45:01,382
We need to keep in mind that

556
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:03,657
if we didn't have royal family
members with great vision

557
00:45:03,658 --> 00:45:05,422
to grant scholarships
to commoners to study,

558
00:45:06,436 --> 00:45:08,102
many soldiers around here

559
00:45:08,302 --> 00:45:10,102
would have been just
a person with no future.

560
00:45:11,292 --> 00:45:12,293
Therefore,

561
00:45:12,838 --> 00:45:14,598
they shouldn't be
ungrateful to the country.

562
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:39,899
(Next Episode)
You know what you just said, right?

563
00:45:39,900 --> 00:45:41,299
I only spoke the truth.

564
00:45:41,300 --> 00:45:46,100
Do you know that if someone overhears you, they
might misunderstand? You could be in danger.

565
00:45:46,900 --> 00:45:50,400
Is... your Highness worried about me?

566
00:45:55,700 --> 00:45:58,799
Take the forces there and
detain all the key royals.

567
00:45:58,800 --> 00:46:01,100
If they enter, shoot them all!

568
00:46:02,500 --> 00:46:05,000
Captain Phobtheera has
already led the troops out.
